      },
      "date": "2019-02-12 22:00:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI have no problem with this change but the truth is lctl tracing is obsolete when compared to the linux kernel ftrace. ftrace can do things like tell you what function is being called with a function pointer. I don't think lustre tracing can do that to my knowledge. We also have to add in these macros everywhere but ftrace can trace anything you want without having to add special macros to the code.",
